# Discord Chat Analysis for 💻-tech-support

## 1. Summary:
The chat segment covers discussions about ElizaOS, plugin functionality, API limitations, and documentation. Snapper shared Episode 2 of the ElizaOS Tutorial, covering CLI usage, project creation, character file setup, and running agents in dev mode. There were questions about plugin-knowledge's inability to perform local embeddings and potential API endpoint changes. ℭ𝔦𝔭𝔥𝔢𝔯 provided positive feedback on documentation quality while suggesting potential improvements like hyperlinking to GitHub packages. A significant discussion occurred regarding Twitter/X API limitations for DMs, with users confirming that the basic tier is severely limited (1 DM per day), making it essentially unusable for agent interactions, while even enterprise pricing has significant limitations. Luke 🇦🇺 reported an issue with the knowledge plugin API endpoints potentially being removed or changed in a recent update.

## 2. FAQ:
Q: Could I ask why the plugin-knowledge isn't able to do local embeddings? (asked by starlord) A: Unanswered
Q: Is this only on Twitter or web client also? (asked by sayonara) A: Unanswered
Q: Was the API endpoints removed on the latest version of plugin-knowledge? (asked by Luke 🇦🇺) A: Unanswered
Q: Am I just misunderstanding things here or do you know if that's true about X API DM limitations? (asked by Luke 🇦🇺) A: Whatever docs says is true. DMs only really enterprise plan level in API. (answered by cjft)

# Discord Chat Analysis for 🥇-partners Channel

## 1. Summary:
The chat primarily focused on discussions about cryptocurrency projects, particularly around launchpads and memecoins. Phenowin provided detailed analysis of successful launchpad strategies, specifically highlighting BONK's approach on Solana. They emphasized the importance of trust, quality KOLs (Key Opinion Leaders), and selective project curation for launchpad success. There was mention of DegenAI being listed on MEXC exchange, with speculation about a potential Gate listing. Community members discussed the competitive landscape of launchpads, comparing strategies from BONK, Believe, and Jupiter. Phenowin suggested that auto.fun's launchpad fees might be too low compared to competitors and recommended studying BONK's successful model. There was also a brief discussion about potentially incorporating gambling features into their launchpad, though Phenowin expressed concerns this might damage trust.

## 2. FAQ:
Q: Is DegenAI listed on MEXC? (implied by Void) A: Yes, DegenAI is MEXC listed (answered by Void)
Q: Gate listing coming for degenai? (asked by Drip) A: Unanswered
Q: What did BONK do right? (implied by human_nalejzpa) A: They built trust through excellent KOLs promoting their launchpad, had big backers/investors, and are part of Solana history (answered by Phenowin)
